message.description:
The main body of the message to a target contact. The message can be customised with dynamic data by using inserts for to add details about the supporter (from field inputs or questions), or about the contact using data from the target record.
#### Inserting supporter data
A supporter inserts can be formulated using a format of *{user_data~Fieldname}*, where **Fieldname** is the name of the field in the account.  e.g {user_data~Email Address}. *standardFieldNames* can not be used for this purpose, however the given names used in the account can be looked up by calling [listSupporterFields](/operations/listSupporterFields).
#### Inserting data about the target contact
A contact record has a number of fields which can be used to provide some customisation for both the content and the subject of a message:


{contact_data~salutation}

 {contact_data~organization}

 {contact_data~positionHeld}

 {contact_data~title}

 {contact_data~firstName}

 {contact_data~lastName}

 {contact_data~suffix}

 {contact_data~faxNumber}

 {contact_data~address1}

 {contact_data~address2}

 {contact_data~address3}

 {contact_data~city}

 {contact_data~region}

 {contact_data~postalCode}

 {contact_data~country}

 {contact_data~partyImgUrl}

 {contact_data~bio1}

 {contact_data~bio2}

 {contact_data~bio3} *(represent the X handle of the contact)*

 {contact_data~bio4}

 {contact_data~bio5}

 {contact_data~bio6}

 {contact_data~bio7}

 {contact_data~bio8} *(represents the Party of the contact)*

